answers.body_markdown:
In my case was a metadata entityID missplacing.

In the IDP metadata file I had, the entityID was wrong. It was, in fact, the value of SP entityID, which was not correct.

Once I fixed it (by setting the correct entityID IDP value) application could establish trust.

So if you don&#39;t know the IDP entityID ask for it to the IDP administrator.

I.E.:

    &lt;md:EntityDescriptor
	xmlns:md=&quot;urn:oasis:names:tc:SAML:2.0:metadata&quot;
	entityID=&quot;&#171;YOUR IDP ENTITY_ID&#187;&quot;
	&gt;
	&lt;md:IDPSSODescriptor protocolSupportEnumeration=&quot;urn:oasis:names:tc:SAML:2.0:protocol&quot; &gt;
		&lt;md:KeyDescriptor xmlns:ds=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/09/xmldsig#&quot; use=&quot;signing&quot;&gt;
    ...

